<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-1882] Aggregator fails permanently if exception thrown from aggregation strategy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-1882</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;BatchSender&lt;/tt&gt; thread in &lt;tt&gt;BatchProcessor&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&apos;t expect any error thrown from &lt;tt&gt;Collection.add()&lt;/tt&gt; method, so when it is thrown the whole thread dies and is never recovered. In Aggregator, where aggregation strategy exists such exceptions can be easily thrown from &lt;tt&gt;Collection.add()&lt;/tt&gt; and can render Aggregator unusable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12485698">CAMEL-1882</key>
            <summary>Aggregator fails permanently if exception thrown from aggregation strategy</summary>
